reviews.text: Below is my original review. It works well, but it has a long delay when turning on the light, and it's just not something I can get used to. Will have to replace it with something else. ======================= It works like you'd expect any dimmer to, but it adds a great feature that most of the leading brands don't: an adjustment button that sets the minimum brightness level. Most dimmers let the lights go completely off when you go to minimum. This switch allows you to set a minimum so that the lowest setting doesn't completely turn the lights off. When you actually want the lights off, you push the switch. It's UL listed, so you can be confident in the safety level. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: I wanted to love it, but just can't get used to the delay
